# Reason: CVE-2025-64756 is a command-injection flaw in glob's CLI (-c/--cmd option).
#          The glob package is an indirect dependency bundled with npm in the base image.
#          npm uses glob as a library and never invokes the vulnerable CLI path.
#          The vulnerability therefore cannot be triggered in this container's use case.
#          A fix is available in glob 10.5.0 / 11.1.0 and will be addressed when the
#          node:22 base image is updated to a version that bundles npm >= 10.9.7.
# Acceptance date: 2026-03-22
CVE-2025-64756

# Reason: CVE-2026-33671 is reported for picomatch, but the node:22-bookworm-slim
#          base image currently bundles picomatch 4.0.2 under npm/tinyglobby,
#          which is the fixed version cited by the advisory. Treating as false
#          positive and suppressing until Trivy advisory metadata is corrected.
# Acceptance date: 2026-04-18
CVE-2026-33671

